val tests must continue to pass.\n- The plan assumes no database schema changes.\n- The repo already contains derived read models relevant to SQL routing: UserWeekFact, TeamWeekRollup, RcdoWeekRollup, CarryForwardFact, ComplianceFact.\n- Duet config in `.pi/duet/config.json` shows static checks: `npm run check:static`; unit checks: `npm test`.\n- There is already an in-progress duet run with modified files under `.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-29T18-32-40-613Z-32faa966/` and tracked changes in `AiController` plus new plan recommendation files.\n\nOpen questions:\n- Should the initial implementation keep the full live traffic experiment service, or trim it down later if it proves too heavy?\n- Which exact models should be treated as control/treatment defaults for LLM and embeddings in the reusable A/B harness?\n- Should analytical SQL routing be limited to clearly aggregate/comparison queries, or should it also handle broader reporting-style questions?\n- How much observability is wanted for prompt caching and chunk-size analysis beyond basic logging/counters?\n- Should the A/B runner compare only LLMs initially, or also embeddings and HyDE in the same reusable harness?\n\nUse this handoff as background context. If it conflicts with the explicit task below or the current repository state, prioritize the explicit task and repo state.\n\nPlan overview:\n{\n  \"goal\": \"Add seven optimization capabilities to the AI pipeline — prompt caching, A/B testing infrastructure, embedding model override (offline eval only), LLM model A/B, HyDE, SQL query routing, and chunk size analysis — all backward-compatible and default-off. The embedding-model A/B experiment is scoped to offline evaluation only (via AbComparisonRunner) because the Pinecone index is fixed at 1536 dimensions matching text-embedding-3-small; routing live queries through text-embedding-3-large (3072-d) would cause dimension mismatches. Backend-only; no frontend, e2e, or schema changes.\",\n  \"totalSteps\": 7,\n  \"step